flowRoot.flowPara: If there are no online accounts with avatars, a stock avatar is selected by default. The action bar allows the colour to be changed.
If there are online accounts with avatars, one is selected. Selecting a stock avatar causes the action bar to slide up, so that the colour can be changed.
When a photo is selected, the dialog becomes an action dialog with Change and Cancel buttons. Handles allow image crop.
First section shows existing or previous profile pictures. Second section shows stock images.
The Cancel button returns to the photo selection grid.
Becomes an action dialog when take a picture is pressed. Main view shows a preview from the camera, and an action bar slides up to show a take picture button.
Once a picture has been taken, it is possible to crop before selecting it. The Take Another button returns to the previous step.
